metadata.title: Pitts Special
aws::graph::propositions: # Pitts Special Aircraft Models and Specifications
Pitts Special uses symmetrical airfoil.
S-1S is a model of Pitts Special.
S-1C is a model of Pitts Special.
S-1C is built by Aerotek.
S-1C is certified for competition aerobatics.
S-1C has a round airfoil section.
S-1C has four ailerons.
S-1C is powered by a 180 hp (134 kW) Lycoming AEIO-360-B4A engine.
61 S-1C aircraft were built.
S-1C is available from Aviat Aircraft as a plans-built aircraft.
S-1SS is a model of Pitts Special.
S-1SS is similar to the certified S-1S "Roundwing".
S-1SS has 180-200+ hp (134-149 kW) power.
S-1SS is a single-seat aircraft.
S-1SS is a homebuilt aircraft.
S-1SS has a symmetrical wing.
S-1SS has four symmetrical "Super-Stinker" style ailerons.
S-1SS has a 300 degree/s roll rate.
S-1SS has a fixed-pitch propeller.
S-1SS is available in plans and components form from Steen Aero Lab.
S-1T is a model of Pitts Special.
S-1T is built by Aerotek.
S-1T is based on the S-1C model.
S-1T has a 200 hp (149 kW) Lycoming AEIO-360-A1E engine.
S-1T has minor changes compared to S-1C.
64 S-1T aircraft were built.

text:
Uses symmetrical airfoil.
S-1S
Aerotek-built certified S-1C for competition aerobatics, round airfoil section, four ailerons, and powered by a 180 hp (134 kW) Lycoming AEIO-360-B4A; 61 built. This model is also available from Aviat Aircraft as a plans-built aircraft.
S-1SS
Similar to the certified S-1S "Roundwing". 180200+ hp (134149 kW), single-seat, homebuilt, symmetrical wing, four symmetrical "Super-Stinker" style ailerons, 300 degree/s roll rate, fixed-pitch propeller. This model is available in plans and components form from Steen Aero Lab.
S-1T
Aerotek-built S-1C with a 200 hp (149 kW) Lycoming AEIO-360-A1E and minor changes; 64 built.
